This is a 30 minute special on the music of the indigenous people of Meso-America (Aztec/Mayan/Toltec etc). It was originally aired on KVCRTV in San Bernadino, CA. I worked with Xavier at Knott&amp;#039;s Berry Farm for a couple years around 1999, and he gave me a video copy of this. I finally transferred it to DVD so I thought I&amp;#039;d share it. (It is an old tape so there is video stress on the edges.) It is footage of Xavier and other musicians in native dress playing on authentic instruments, and there is a short bit with dancing near the end.

Included is a DVD case insert I created from the VHS insert and a disc label I put together.

Please visit Xavier Quijas Yxayotl&amp;#039;s website at: http://www.yxayotl.com/
